## Quick start with the exemple

1. Wire the encoder: pin A and pin B to two GPIOs, the third pin to GND.
2. Copy the `Encoder_lib/` folder into your project's `lib/` folder.
3. Copy the Encoder_Exemple.cpp in your src

## Content

- **`Encoder.h`** the public interface (what you `#include`) and the doc.
- **`Encoder.cpp`** the implementation (the actual logic).
- **`Encoder_Exemple.cpp`**  a ready-to-run example that print in serial -> Clockwise/Counterclockwise.
Simply Copy its contents into your `src/main.cpp` to test the library right away.
